race.comment: BOOM SHOT (1) was well in the betting over this track and trip last time out and didn't let supporters down with a solid victory. Gets the deadly Gollan/Maloney combination and can go back-to-back without surprising. HEMAN (4) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome at the latest effort but go on the strong win over this course and distance when resuming. Capable of bouncing back. Former Victorian CENTENNIAL PARK (10) was a touch plain in the first run for the new stable but will have come on with that run now in the locker. Will find this easier than what he faced down south and can improve sharply on that first-up effort. TEN GOOD REASONS (13) hails from a handy family (half to G2 winner and 2xG1 placed Osipenko) and has only missed a drum once in eight career efforts. Has to be included. GUNROOM (12) brings NSW formlines to the table and may earn some minor money.
